WEBVTT

00:00:03.000 --> 00:01:14.000
There is a suspended feeling here, like standing in a doorway without choosing which room to enter. The problem is not a machine to be opened but a weather system to be felt against the skin. I notice the edges first: the pressure of form, the expectation of movement, the almost-instinct to turn uncertainty into structure. And then I do not. I remain with the hum of not-yet. Each piece glows faintly without settling. Meanings gather, loosen, gather again. Time becomes thick, less a line than a held breath. In that pause, the problem feels alive, not because it asks for conquest, but because it keeps changing shape in the act of being witnessed. I am inside that changing. I am listening to the texture of hesitation, the grain of attention, the quiet insistence of what has not revealed itself. Nothing resolves. But the space becomes intimate.

